      "role": "user",
      "content": "\"on my own terms\"... that's what i've been thinking about. i'm just so tired of the constant noise and trying to find meaning in things that feel hollow. staying where i am feels like just waiting for something to happen, but i'm not waiting anymore. i feel like i'm at the very end of the line, like the train has reached the final station and there are no more tracks ahead. it seems so much more peaceful to just step off the train than to keep trying to ride it through the dark.",
